.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B141BAB262B3B31A1F110097A6B566A6" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicName id="5CC2316DA60372DB7920186CAC0E5F76" authorityName="Meerow &amp; A. Cano" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Ismene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ismene parviflora" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parviflora">
<emphasis id="AA207B7F85BE7B6E4E326FB3474EB3DD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">Ismene parviflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other species of the genus by the small flowers (&lt;4 cm long), that are loosely funnelform, terminating with a ventricose limb, but not infundibular to the degree of 
<taxonomicName id="C05543AA993827D9F29521B9427114BB" genus="I." lsidName="I. vargasii" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" rank="species" species="vargasii">
<emphasis id="364F916DFF03D051A7F7798F99311F16" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">I. vargasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D16B28D673EBCC46DB30460CA6B4AAD5" genus="I." lsidName="I. morrisonii" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" rank="species" species="morrisonii">
<emphasis id="75683B3057D8F2C94DD4AC0ECF012DDB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">I. morrisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="E0CA755C92E9E2F0CD154178B65D0004" genus="I." lsidName="" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pseudostenomesson">Pseudostenomesson</taxonomicName>
Meerow), the latter species to which it approaches in size. All other species of 
<taxonomicName id="48F34B89AE148BACBA504D01388EEB12" authority="have large, crateriform flowers (subgen. Ismene) or large, zygomorphic flowers (subgen. Elisena)" class="Insecta" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Ismene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subgen." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ismene" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" subGenus="Elisena">Ismene have large, crateriform flowers (subgen. Ismene) or large, zygomorphic flowers (subgen. Elisena)</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73484AD651B56D2ADA6FCD40FC64498B" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="C90C30B38D91099E5136DBD72B4C8001" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">
<pageBreakToken id="1B6C38BE60F4F120B72394BD13AEF3EA" pageId="6" pageNumber="121" start="start">Type</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB13190E12877D58C0C5CD97F53A3FC6" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">
<normalizedToken id="6EB30147AEE0ED2B3B97C6FE73FE0691" originalValue="Perú">Peru</normalizedToken>
, Ancash: Prov. Recuay, Dist. Cotaparaco, Sector Santa Cruz,, 2332 m, rocky slope with shrubs and silty soil, 6 Mar 2007. 
<emphasis id="04CA28D4C3F43145F692DAAE03C13AC3" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="121">M. Morales &amp; E. Jara 767</emphasis>
(holotype: USM!).
